[SN]TITLE[SN]
Two taken to hospital after Anglesey lightning strikes

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A woman and boy have been taken to hospital following lightning strikes at a house on Anglesey.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
North Wales Fire and Rescue Service was called at 06:27 BST to Rhostrehwfa, near Llangefni, on Tuesday.
The first strike hit a shed which caused a small fire and the second struck the chimney which then collapsed.
The Welsh Ambulance Service said the woman and boy were taken to Ysbyty Gwynedd with minor injuries.
